Brand new, never installed. I decided to go another direction with my build.

Kit has everything you need to replace the standard gas system in your AR-15 and convert it to a reliable, positive-cycling, gas piston system. Eliminates venting of hot gases and powder residue into the bolt carrier and receiver for reduced fouling and less wear on the action. Feeds more smoothly, maintenance is easier, and the gun runs cooler, too. Short-stroke piston shaft eliminates concussive gas expansion in the upper receiver for less violent cycling and reduced felt recoil. Easy to adjust for three levels of gas release: normal fire, firing with a suppressor attached, or a single round fired without cycling. Picatinny rail on the gas block provides mounting space for a variety of front sights. Installation requires removal of original gas block, but no permanent alterations to barrel or upper receiver. Remove the piston system at any time and reinstall the original parts. Replacement handguard provides extra internal clearance for piston rod and has internal shield to protect your hand from heat buildup during sustained fire.

Hello, Hope your having a great day.

Today I am selling my Advantage Arms Gen 3 Glock 17/22 - .22lr Conversion Kit. This kit also will fit a Glock 17L, G22, G31, G34, G35, G37. (This kit will not work with any Gen 4 glock, the design is different in some ways and are not compatible with the new style design). Previously I purchased the same type of kit but from a different company (Tactical Solutions). I had nothing but trouble with that product because their slide is made of Steel. The Advantage Arms slide is made of Aluminum which is the perfect amount of mass to be pushed back by any .22lr round, therefore not one problem whatsoever with any type of ammo.

This is a Glock Gen 3 slide conversion kit that can be installed by simply removing the slide off of your current handgun and putting the Advantage Arms .22lr version slide on to your beloved Glock frame the same way, load the 10rd. magazine and you are ready to shoot .22lr caliber rounds. Included in the box is the 10rd magazine and a speed loader (just like the stock loader in the Glock boxes when you purchase them). The magazine works flawlessly and have not had one issue with feeding, stovepipes, anything. 

This is a great option for training. This package helps a shooter: young, female or male get used to the grip and the feel of the handgun without the recoil or the price we all pay for the expensive centerfire ammo (9mm, 40 S&W, .45 ACP) just to practice.

Everything when purchased is still inside the original box and not altered in anyway. Some parts not even used.

This kit is not picky with any brand of ammunition and is a blast to plink around without damaging the pocketbook. It is in mint condition and not one scratch on the slide in anyway. title: For Sale:  Armalite AR50-A1
postcontent:
So, you want to shoot with the big boys? Here is everything you need to get into 50BMG shooting. All you have to do is add your scope and begin having fun !! If you have been looking into the 50BMG game you know there is much more to it, than just buying the gun and running down to WalMart for some ammo. 
In this extensive package you have one of the most accurate 50BMG bolt guns available, the Armalite AR50A1 with .7 MOA accuracy!! This Big Boy comes complete with a Picatinny rail 15 MOA scope base, Schilen Standard Single Stage trigger, custom mono pod and Bipod adaptor (so any Harris type bipod can be used), and of course all the paper work and tools that came with the rifle from Armalite. Additional extras include: over 120 pieces of once fired brass, 120 armor piercing bullets , 50 Speer FMJ bullets, 20 rounds of loaded ammo, 2 pounds of 50BMG powder, 2 boxes of 100 count CCI 50BMG primers (these are $50 each if you can find them) , a Lee 50BMG press with dies, case trimmer and mounting block. The rifle breaks down to fit into two included hard cases for transport and storage. Add all this together and you have a package that would run well over $4,500. This gun has been fired fewer than 20 times, it is like new, with extras, and can be yours for $3,500.
